Organizes Mis en Place.
Cleans and prepares condiments.
Obtains adequate quantities of linen from the linen room as per the request sheet.
Follows the set service standards while serving the guest.
Ensures sufficient quantities of crockery, cutlery, china and glassware is available prior to the service operation.
Ensure orders are thoroughly checked before serving to the guest.
Assists the Captain at all times.
Ensures proper stacking of trays on the side station.
To take note of the menus including the daily specials.
Interacts with guests in each of the outlets to solicit comments.
Communicates with the Outlet Manager/Head Waiter any difficulties, guest comments and other relevant information.
To maintain discreet observation of guests for signals where they may need assistance.
To demonstrate the 12-Service Excellence Basics.
Keeps updated with new products in the market.
